that‚Äôs what makes this all so terrifying. do these people really believe that tom hanks and hillary clinton are personally running a massive pedophilia ring? really??? but consider this: trump announced at a rally this week that the farmers being harmed by his stupid trade war had told him ‚Äúwe can take it.‚Äù no actual farmers said that to him. we all know that. but it‚Äôs a little thing, just pa of the story we are all interacting with.

the pulsating hea of the qanon theory is not a lunatic fringe denying the real consequences of a failing presidency. the hea of it is a devoted fan base constructing elaborate theories to make the story more fun and engaging. and if you sta from the premise that nothing government does matters, then it‚Äôs easy to come along for the ride. there‚Äôs no real difference between hillary clinton and the smoke monster. they‚Äôre both just characters on the television.

that‚Äôs what alarms me most about the growth of qanon. it‚Äôs not that these people are unhinged and possibly armed. it‚Äôs that we‚Äôve lost the capacity to treat civics, goverce, and public affairs as though they have actual stakes with actual consequences. the premise of the trump presidency is that nothing matters, so you should root for your side and heckle the opposing team. he encourages his suppoers to treat democrats and journalists like a rival fan base.

as fans of @rkelly and viewers of ‚Äúsurviving r. kelly‚Äù (@lifetimetv) digest and react to the docuseries, the organization @colorofchange has called for r. kelly‚Äôs longtime record label @rcarecords to drop the r&b king immediately.  according to the group: rca has relished in the publicity and intentionally popularized an image of r. kelly as a palatable sex symbol, rather than the sexual predator he is.  some see #muterkelly as a bright success because spotify removed the singer from its curated playlists; but getting r. kelly dropped from rca may not be easy or immediate.  r. kelly has recorded for the rca label group since he was a member of public announcement - his entire career.  although he hasn‚Äôt released a major studio album since 2015, his contract is probably so lucrative, rca has to handle the situation carefully if they no longer want to release new material from kelly.  i doubt his contract could just lapse without consequence for either party.  lauryn hill hasn‚Äôt recorded for columbia and still can‚Äôt use her namely solely.  if anything, rca will probably have to buy out r. kelly to terminate his contract since he‚Äôs made so much money for rca and parent company @sony over the years.  a buyout would also include r. kelly owning his masters as well as his camp and legal team will claim he hadn‚Äôt been convicted of any crimes.  it‚Äôll be interesting to see how the demise of r. kelly will play out.  meanwhile, it‚Äôs been reported that his streaming numbers are up.  he also released a new song this weekend via soundcloud.

text:
a few years ago i made the biggest change ever in my life by deciding to break free from a toxic relationship that was killing me physically, mentally, emotionally, and spiritually. since then,  i've had to adjust and survive as a single mother of three along with juggling day to day obstacles. but, i learned how to make it work and have been living a happier and healthier life since. now, i'm no stranger to overcoming challenges and leaving a toxic relationship was just one of the many struggles i've had to overcome. ***
join on january 16 @ 7pm est for my free webinar (linktree in bio) where we will discuss the tools and resources i used to walk away from a toxic relationship, become a published author, and begin the journey to creating the life i always wanted. the first five people to sign up will receive a free copy of my book let mia tell it and everyone will receive my 30 day breaking toxic cycles journal for free! ***
i can't wait to grow and elevate with you and assist you with breaking the cycles that has been holding you back and keeping you from living your best life! *select the linktree in my bio to sign up!!!!!

text:
the movement, ‚Äúescape the corset,‚Äù began with women posting photos on social media of smashed makeup palettes ‚Äî colorful messes of shimmering powder and crushed lipstick that looked almost like beautiful works of art.

so what are women who are escaping the corset doing, exactly? aside from trashing makeup, which is saving them hundreds of dollars a month, they are embracing bowl haircuts and opting for eyeglasses instead of contacts ‚Äî a seemingly simple protest that, nonetheless, has made the women targets of verbal abuse and death threats online.

text: mentoring is one of my favorite things in gymnastics and skydiving. i love to give back. this red bull fly girls event reminded me of why i skydive and how much i love it! just thinking back on the times my female mentors (amy, sara, mel curtis, melissa lowe) embraced my ‚Äúnewness‚Äù and made a lasting impression with a camp or even just a single jump. thank you! and this weekend i jumped with ladies, some with only 80 freefly jumps, some with little confidence in their abilities, even a guy with just a handful of head down jumps...and we managed a 10 way vertical formation with him!! they all made me smile as i watched them smile!! üòÅ sometimes a little appreciation goes a long way. robby, mx, and mikey knight taught me that much...and how fortunate i was to learn from ‚Äúthe godfathers‚Äù of vertical sequential flying!! they would all be proud as their words still stick firmly in my head & heart as we pass their wisdom to the next generation of badasses! live & love bigzzzzzz forever! üíö thank you red bull for this wonderful opportunity to give back! #redbullflygirls #redbull #liquidskysports #floridaweather #skydivedeland #metoo #metoomovement #givesyouwings #empoweringwomen #2019

text:
in 2019, your actions are making the difference!
.
.
.
with organized, persistent effort at the local level, the nation‚Äôs voice was able to impact the political will of a justice system currently designed to bend toward patriarchal power and mass incarceration at the national level. from civic society organizations, grass root social activists, to celebrities and congress members ‚Äî americans came together to enforce measured justice in place of the harsh legislative charges made upon a young woman of color and victim of sex trafficking, cyntoia brown. .
.
.
today, just days until tennessee governor bill haslam term‚Äôs ending on january 19, 2019, @governorbillhaslam granted cyntoia brown, the now 30-year-old, clemency from the first-degree premeditated and first-degree felony murder she was convicted of and tried for as an adult, at the age of 16 in 2004. .
.
.
according to aljazeera, nashville mayor david bailey praised haslam‚Äôs decision, calling it a ‚Äú‚Ä¶great day for social justice and our city‚Äù and democrat stacey abrams @staceyabrams tweeted, ‚Äújustice has finally been served‚Ä¶this victory belongs to cyntoia brown and to the tennessee human trafficking activists, especially black women, who refused to concede to injustice and instead organized to create change.‚Äù .
.
.
your voice matters. your voice is the change that you‚Äôve been waiting for. get organized and act, everyone. .
.
.
you raise. we rise. #theamericanmom .
.

text:
hey ladies! amber gould and amanda desjardins are stoked to be co-facilitating this year's 2019 international womens day art show. squamish edition!  this year's theme is 'exposure'. we arrived at the theme after a very long, cool conversation about the positive experience of bringing the inside out. there are many hidden sub surface layers within each woman. we believe that artistic expression can catalyze the process of bringing these hidden parts of ourselves into our conscious awareness.
this is a safe form of exposure that is the result of a powerful and  autonomous process in which the artist has full control over what she chooses to expose. this chosen form of exposure can serve to support the healing and growth of the artist and will challenge and positively transform her experience.
we will now be accepting entries and pushing the submission deadline to feb 24th. we encourage artwork from creatives and self proclaimed artist of any kind. no experience necessary.
.
expose your exposure.
.
contact us at womensdayartshow2015@gmail.com
amanda- 604 848 5348
amber-778 970 1264 to receive 
show guidelines and entry form. .
.
.

#singingforsafety challenge!üé∂üé§üôèüèºüíñ
.
in honor of all survivors, and as someone who is a survivor of sexual assault, this is a cause very close to my heart. üôèüèº
i believe that survivors having resources is vitally important, so i hope that you can help me in supporting this valuable nonprofit organization advocating for survivors & against sexual assault.
(rainn.org/national sexual assault hotline)
üôèüèº
i pray that others can find the courage, strength, and support they need while healing/surviving, and i also hope that this challenge can raise awareness and inspire those who need it most. speak your truth, say it out loud, regardless of others judgements!
üôèüèº
want to join me in singing for safety??
here's how it works:

1.post of video of you singing your favorite empowerment/inspirational song.(dont worry about how you look or sound, the point is to fearlessly speak your truth!!) 2.tag at least 2 other people in the challenge i.e. "@serena.maureen i challenge you to #singingforsafety !!" 3.go to gofundme.com/singing-for-safety donate at least $5(or more) and share the link with your friends and family. the challenge will be going until the end of the month.

don't like to sing and dont want to post a video?? that's ok! you can still donate to the cause, 100% proceeds goes directly to rainn!

thank you so much again for supporting survivors!!üíñüíúüíôüíöüíõüß°

por nate raymond 
nantucket, eeuu¬†(reuters) - el exprotagonista de "house of cards" kevin spacey compareci√≥ el lunes ante un tribunal de massachusetts para enfrentar la acusaci√≥n de haber abusado sexualmente de un joven de 18 a√±os tras atiborrarlo de alcohol en un bar en nantucket hace m√°s de dos a√±os.

el actor ganador del oscar no hizo un acuerdo para declararse culpable con la corte de distrito de nantucket tras ser acusado el mes pasado de un delito por abuso y agresi√≥n. 
spacey dijo en documentos judiciales que planea declararse no culpable.

vestido de traje gris y corbata, spacey no habl√≥ durante la corta audiencia previa al juicio. un juez le orden√≥ no contactar a su supuesta v√≠ctima.

nantucket, una isla tur√≠stica costa afuera de massachusetts que usualmente es tranquila a comienzos de enero, estaba llena de camiones de cadenas de televisi√≥n el lunes.

el actor de 59 a√±os es uno de decenas de hombres de los sectores empresarial, de la pol√≠tica y el entretenimiento que han sido acusados de conductas sexuales inapropiadas desde que las acusaciones contra el productor cinematogr√°fico harvey weinstein en 2017 dieron origen al movimiento #metoo.

spacey se vio envuelto en una gran controversia despu√©s de que el actor anthony rapp lo acus√≥ en octubre de 2017 de intentar seducirlo en 1986, cuando rapp ten√≠a 14 a√±os.

el actor se disculp√≥ con rapp por su conducta inapropiada. la controversia llev√≥ a que spacey, ganador del oscar en 2000 por su papel en "american beauty", saliera de la serie de netflix "house of cards", as√≠ como de la pel√≠cula "all the money in the world". el actor kevin spacey (al centro en la imagen) en la corte de distrito de nantucket en nantucket, eeuu, ene 7, 2019. 
reuters

la acusaci√≥n de nantucket se conoci√≥ por vez primera en noviembre de 2017, por medio de la experiodista televisiva de boston heather unruh, que dijo a reporteros que spacey manose√≥ a su hijo adolescente el 7 de julio de 2016 en el restaurante y bar club car, donde trabajaba como camarero.

bennett college made me into the woman i am today.  dean scarlett taught us to respect ourselves as young women, i gained the courage to run for office sophomore and and junior year and then become sga president my senior year.  my parents wondered, ‚Äúwhere did this michelle come from.‚Äù i learned to be a fearless leader at bennett.  i produced the first $1 gym jam in the coffee house at bennett that people were talking about for weeks. fearless! i then took my fearlessness to philly for grad school, then la for work and then to the big apple.  without bennett, i would not be running a business for 10+ years with success.  i am bennett made, bennett proud! please support my alma mater and donate to keep the doors open.  as you see in the news with the #metoo #muterkelly movements, women‚Äôs colleges are needed now more than ever.  thanks to my friends @amandaseales @jamalhbryant for your support and i want you to join us in raising monies for @bennett_college!  #istandwithbennett #bennettstrong #bennettbelles @bennettcollegenaa1926
name: Bennett College Alumnae

text:

option 2: i‚Äôm strong, a survivor, nonjudgmental. i am beautiful, and unique. i value myself for who i am in this moment - for where i came from, and where i‚Äôm going. i see beauty, and understand pain. i am perfect with all eccentricities.
‚ú®
it takes work babe. it doesn‚Äôt happen overnight. time and persistence are your best friends. one day you‚Äôll wake up, and you won‚Äôt hear the voice. you‚Äôll be excited to greet the day.

you are stronger than you know. we need people like you in this world. ily. üíï

text: today my sweet tribe at @fredandfar asked me to send them my childhood authentic self. and i gladly did. such a great reminder of the carefree and innocent minded girl i was before the world had its way with me. both of these photos were taken before i turned 10 years old. before trauma hit me and i learned at age 14 that monsters are not under our beds, but smiling in our faces. a time before i learned that despite having parents that filled me with love, you could even have grandparents that would ask you to suppress your truth to keep peace and reputations as they want them to be seen. before i grew into the self-confident and determined woman that i am, there were many years that occurred between these images and waking up one day, choosing myself. i wear my truth like a badge of honor because i realized in my early-thirties that only warriors who survive get to wear that badge. there is no reason to ever hide what made you the person that you are, and if anyone asks you to meet their expectations because your truth is too difficult for them, just smile and tell them ‚Äòno‚Äô. thank you, @fredandfar for reminding me of the young girl that had dreams and innocence and goals and a shine in her that the world attempted to disarm. those expectations collect dust now, not my heart. that spirited child is still in my soul. and let me tell you, my inner child can be a little shit sometimes. but she is free and daily filling her own cup with as much self-love that she can muster. life experiences can be beautiful and magical, i will never allow the ugly pieces to take away this young being who will continue to grasp what she set out to accomplish. and i damn sure will never allow my own daughter (and son) to hide themselves either.üîª#authentic #childhood #authenticself #younggirl #child #fredandfar #tribe #mytribe #selflove #selfcare #truth #empowerment #empoweringwomen #theabcsofselflove #spirited #strength #warrior #badgeofhonor #speakup #metoo #me #selfconfidence #expectations #yourtruth #yourstory #mine #buildeachotherup #beanicehuman #bekindtoyourself #babewiththepower

text: there are many reasons to learn martial arts. not only do they teach people humility, confidence and respect‚Äîthey also teach people how to defend themselves in dangerous situations. jiu jitsu, wrestling, judo, kickboxing, and other core parts of modern day mma are valuable skills because they are based on live sparring with resistance. this story of @ufc strawweight fighter @polyanaviana showcases why these martial arts can be so empowering for women (who are disproportionately at risk for sexual assaults and other crimes at the hands of men). apparently, this guy threatened her with a firearm and tried to mug her. she threw a couple punches, a kick, and then secured back control and the rear naked choke to subdue her attacker until police arrived. teaching girls to fight isn‚Äôt the only answer to solving violence against women (in an ideal world, men wouldn‚Äôt attack women, but this isn‚Äôt the world we live in), but it is a practical skill that can save a person‚Äôs life. and as viana‚Äôs attacker knows all too well‚Äîit can also be very empowering. if you‚Äôve ever considered training, go give it a try. it‚Äôs life changing. if you‚Äôre in toronto, check out @girlswhofight_to üëäüèºü•ã#bjj #jiujitsu #bjjgirls #ufc #mma #fight #brasil #strongwomen #inspiration #martialarts #bjjlifestyle #selfdefense #crime #violence #girlswhofight #confidence #power #riseandgrind #hustle #mondaymotivation #newyearsresolution #toronto #the6 #the6ix #fitness #health #exercise #metoo

text:
we‚Äôre all smiles, but it didn‚Äôt used to be that way.

a week before this trip my family was doing an emergency rescue. i was broken. i didn‚Äôt have the energy to keep playing my part.

as x continued to ‚Äúdo what he wanted, with whomever he wanted, whenever he wanted‚Äù, i was falling apart.

my weight plummeted to 90lbs. i cried almost every hour on this trip. yes, in the middle of disney.

and my family mourned for me. over the loss of who i was, and the shell of a person i had become.

it wasn‚Äôt until years after, that i finally left (yes, i went back). it wasn‚Äôt until recently that i starting seeing and feeling the progress.

this is not the end babe. it might feel like the world is crashing down. and to a point, it is. but, it gets better, i promise.

don‚Äôt ever give up.

text:
(cnn) cyntoia denise brown, a woman serving a life sentence for killing a man who bought her for sex when she was 16 years old, has been granted clemency, the tennessee governor's office said monday.

brown, 30, will be released to parole supervision on august 7 after serving 15 years in prison, gov. bill haslam's office said in a statement. "this decision comes after careful consideration of what is a tragic and complex case," haslam said. "cyntoia brown committed, by her own admission, a horrific crime at the age of 16. yet, imposing a life sentence on a juvenile that would require her to serve at least 51 years before even being eligible for parole consideration is too harsh, especially in light of the extraordinary steps ms. brown has taken to rebuild her life. transformation should be accompanied by hope." brown's case drew the attention of several high-profile advocates including a us congressman, several tennessee lawmakers and a number of a-list celebrities. comedian amy schumer, reality star kim kardashian west and actress ashley judd were among those who called for brown's clemency.

in 2004, brown killed johnny mitchell allen, who brown said had solicited her for sex and taken her back to his house.

prosecutors at the time said brown shot allen in the head while he was sleeping, stole money and guns, took his truck, and fled the scene. they argued the killing wasn't motivated by self-defense, but robbery.

brown said she was scared for her life by allen's behavior, and took money for fear of returning empty-handed to her pimp, nicknamed "cut throat." a juvenile court found brown competent to be tried as an adult. she was convicted of murder and robbery, and sentenced to life in prison.

full story: https://www-m.cnn.com/2019/01/07/us/tennessee-cyntoia-brown-granted-clemency/index.html?r=https%3a%2f%2fwww.google.com%2f

brown, 30, will be released to parole supervision on august 7 after serving 15 years in prison, gov. bill haslam's office said in a statement. "this decision comes after careful consideration of what is a tragic and complex case," haslam said. "cyntoia brown committed, by her own admission, a horrific crime at the age of 16. yet, imposing a life sentence on a juvenile that would require her to serve at least 51 years before even being eligible for parole consideration is too harsh, especially in light of the extraordinary steps ms. brown has taken to rebuild her life. transformation should be accompanied by hope." brown's case drew the attention of several high-profile advocates including a us congressman, several tennessee lawmakers and a number of a-list celebrities. comedian amy schumer, reality star kim kardashian west and actress ashley judd were among those who called for brown's clemency.

in 2004, brown killed johnny mitchell allen, who brown said had solicited her for sex and taken her back to his house.

prosecutors at the time said brown shot allen in the head while he was sleeping, stole money and guns, took his truck, and fled the scene. they argued the killing wasn't motivated by self-defense, but robbery.

brown said she was scared for her life by allen's behavior, and took money for fear of returning empty-handed to her pimp, nicknamed "cut throat." a juvenile cou found brown competent to be tried as an adult. she was convicted of murder and robbery, and sentenced to life in prison.

#cyntoiabrown #billhaslam #justice #blacklivesmatter #metoo #clemency4cyntoiabrown

text:
the docu-series was difficult to watch. especially as a survivor of rape. i was raped in 1980, on my way to school. i was 14. especially  as a survivor of domestic/intimate partner abuse. for two years i endured unspeakable emotional and physical abuse. often times fearing for my life. things happened that i am not prepared to speak about publicly.
it took a huge amount of courage for these women to come forward knowing the risks, the backlash, the accusations, and the risks to their safety. 
when do we hold the perpetrators accountable? trust me when i tell you, as a survivor who made a bad choice to not follow the rules to a tee and ended up getting raped, i have punished myself a 1000 times over. but, that did not give that grown man the right to force himself on me. i just was a girl who wanted to walk with my peers. i did not deserve what happened to me. but, the truth is, there will always be a part of me that still blames myself.
please take a stand!!! #muterkelly #metoomovement #metoo

text:
i've unfollowed and blocked several accounts in the last couple days reading tasteless jokes about monsters and the victimsleft in their wake.

i get it - we find current events and poke fun at them to belittle their impact on us. but we can't let the impact of atrocious behaviour stop impacting us because when it does that behavior becomes normal. and normal creates an environment where horrible monsters feel safe to roam and be... horrible monsters.

joking about it also belittles the experience of those who've trembled in the hands of these monsters, who feared for their safety and sometimes their lives.

i'm not seeking to be a killjoy but the idea that our empathy has been usurped for a few likes or laughs is one i refuse to believe is true.

forget the narrative of "what if it was your mother/daughter/sister/aunt/girlfriend," and instead remember that a person is a person regardless of their familial tie or relationship status. and as a person they deserve certain things. like a safe space to be, or when needed, to heal.

we help each other heal when we hear each other speak and who wants speak their vulnerable truth with the fear of being mocked and laughed at atop the other inherent fears of their situation/experience right? right.
‚ô•

text:
on jan. 1 a new law went into effect in ireland, making psychological and emotional abuse in intimate partner relationships a crime. similar laws are already on the books in france, england, wales and scotland, who have also criminalized such ‚Äúcoercive control.‚Äù as american trauma psychologists, we want to jump up and down and applaud such efforts. though our hands are clapping, our feet won‚Äôt let us leave the ground. why? because these laws need teeth and backbone. let us explain.

psychological abuse has received considerably less empirical and clinical attention than other forms of interpersonal partner violence. perhaps this is because in the u.s., there are still debates within and among the mental health and legal professions as to its exact definition.

https://youwillbearwitness.com/2019/01/06/irish-law-making-making-psychological-and-emotional-abuse-a-crime-is-commendable/  #metoo #youwillbearwitness #ptsd #peterfox #ptsdsurvivor #ptsdrecovery #ptsdawareness #stopracism #stopbullying #stopchildabuse #trauma #doitfordolly #therapydog #dissociativeidentitydisorder
